On the way to Ferguson, Ferrell engaged her daughter in a dialogue - dressed in a floral sweater and the same floral headband - about a subject they had discussed many times before - the black experience.
"Remember how I taught you about how black people had to fight for what they believed in?"
We're on our way to Ferguson right now because the police killed an 18-year-old, and that's not right.
"It was never in the question not to take her with me", Ferrell later said.
Today's events are the culmination of what happened in the past.
She had to know and see it with her own eyes and grow up with it.
She needed to develop not only in activism and organizing, but also to learn the difference between the different layers of the black experience and what we need to do to free ourselves.
