Folayan has already teamed up with co-director Damon Davis, a highly regarded local artist who deals with death row inmates.
His involvement in the project also interested Ferrell and six other locals who were followed by the Whose Streets? team in the years following Brown's murder.
"No one speaks for us in this document, but it is our statement", Davis said.
