For someone so fascinated by old papers, the support of the National Trust and the Arts Council England and the opportunity to spend almost four months at the castle is almost like a dream.
Rhodes spent his time exploring the Victorian New Castle, going through the archives and studying the many treasures and curiosities, such as the hyena's head on the wall and the bottles that had been thrown into the ditch for centuries.
