The brewery, first mentioned in 1586, has a Renaissance core and was converted to steam power in the nineteenth century.
The years of prosperity followed, when the brewery was famous for its dark beers.
Unfortunately, production was halted during World War II and the brewery was nationalized in 1984.
Since then, the buildings have been used as state property.
